    <Title>Practicing Traffic Management Operative (TMO)</Title>
    <Summary>We are seeking a dedicated and experienced Practicing Traffic Management Operative(TMO) to join our team. As a TMO</Summary>
    <Description><![CDATA[<strong>Job Description:</strong> We are seeking a dedicated and experienced Practicing Traffic Management Operative (TMO) to join our team. As a TMO, you will be responsible for ensuring the safe and efficient flow of traffic in designated areas. Your primary duties will include implementing traffic control measures, coordinating with local authorities, and responding to emergencies as needed.<br><br> <strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br> <ul> <li>Implement traffic management plans in accordance with local regulations and project requirements.</li> <li>Operate traffic control equipment such as traffic lights, signs, and barricades.</li> <li>Direct traffic at intersections and construction sites to ensure the safety of workers and motorists.</li> <li>Monitor traffic flow and adjust control measures as necessary to prevent congestion.</li> <li>Coordinate with law enforcement agencies and emergency responders during incidents and accidents.</li> <li>Communicate effectively with team members and stakeholders to ensure seamless traffic management operations.</li> <li>Conduct regular inspections of traffic control devices and report any malfunctions or damage.</li> <li>Provide assistance and directions to motorists as needed.</li> </ul> <strong>Requirements:</strong><br> <ul> <li>Proven experience as a Traffic Management Operative or similar role.</li> <li>Thorough understanding of traffic laws, regulations, and control techniques.</li> <li>Certification as a Practicing Traffic Management Operative(TMO) is needed.</li> <li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills.</li> <li>Ability to remain calm and focused in high-pressure situations.</li> <li>Physically fit and able to work outdoors in various weather conditions.</li> <li>Must have a Class 1 driver licence.</li> </ul> <br> <strong>Benefits:</strong><br> <ul> <li>Weekly pay.</li> <li>Opportunities for career advancement.</li> <li>Contribution to public safety and community well-being.</li> <li>Positive and team-oriented work environment.</li> <li>Potential temp to perm for the right candidate</li> </ul> <br> <strong>How to Apply:</strong><br><br> If you are passionate about ensuring traffic safety and enjoy working in a dynamic environment, we'd love to have you join our team! Please submit your resume along with a brief cover letter outlining your interest in the Traffic Controller position.<br><br> <strong>Applicants for this position should have NZ residency or a valid NZ work visa.</strong><br><br> Remarkable People is a New Zealand owned and operated recruitment company, founded in Central Otago in 2016. We have grown from one branch to now cover most of New Zealand. We work hard in all aspects of our business. We are passionate about what we do and have our finger on the pulse which is a key factor to the success of Remarkable People.<br> &nbsp;&nbsp;<br> Whilst growth is important to us, we haven&rsquo;t lost sight of the importance of supporting our communities throughout our journey. Remarkable People thrive on supporting our local communities as well as caring for our environment&rsquo;s health, wellbeing, and protection. We strive to bring our communities on our journey with us as we build Remarkable Kiwi&rsquo;s throughout New Zealand.<br> &nbsp;&nbsp;<br> Remarkable People care about their people, regularly encouraging our employees to maintain a healthy balance to ensure they are looking after their health and wellbeing. A healthy work-life balance is key to employees living a lifestyle that is healthy both at work and at home.<br> &nbsp;&nbsp;<br> We love what we do, we have fun, and we smash the mould!<br> &nbsp;&nbsp;<br> Register with the Remarkable People team today and gain instant access to a wide range of job vacancies.]]></Description>
